data.text: In the Far East, the vast Chinese empire made billions of coins during the times of the Romans. Surprisingly affordable, each of these coins called “cash” features a center hole, a numismatic tradition that continues to this day. Coins date to the first five centuries A.D. and made under various dynasties. These coins are different groups and dynasties which have been mixed together to give each customer the possibility of variety.
